posts.description:
I didn't marry their son but I'm still their daughter. Many years have past but everything is still the same. 
I credit so much of who I am today to my ex. I love the woman I am so I'm eternally grateful. He saw the beauty within me I didn't know I had. He saw it before he knew my name. He said the first time he saw me it was like I had wings. I glowed he said. Half mermaid, half angel, all woman.  He said he didn't even know what he wanted but when I walked past the pool that day it was me he wanted. Period. 
I became very soft because of him, very confident in my skin because he celebrated every ounce of me, and most importantly he taught me how to love which I otherwise I had no idea. I didn't even believe being " in love" was a real thing. Although we are on good terms , by his choice we have zero communication but I have forever gained a family. A mother and sister who love me as their own and a father which I've never had (except my uncle and you Allan) who looks at me as I am a gift to his family, even still . Family is family. Love is love. 
We all meet for a reason . We came from two different worlds. And although we are no longer I met  him to show me what life could really be like and to give me more people loving and protecting me. üôè If you're ever wondering why I'm single , ask yourself, how many men have looked at you that way ? Exactly. I have lived a fairytale , been treated like a queen and supported by a man I also adored. When you have experienced what I have , there is  no experiencing less. I believe in magic. 
#atriptoremember #mymexico
